# 4. **Terms of Trade: The Single Most Important AUD Driver**

Terms of trade (TOT) = Export prices / Import prices
Australia = exports **iron ore, coal, LNG**, imports **manufactures**.

![Image](https://d3fy651gv2fhd3.cloudfront.net/charts/australia-exports-of-iron-ore-concentrates.png?h=400\&ismobile=1\&lbl=0\&s=auexioca\&v=202404061100V20230410\&w=640\&utm_source=chatgpt.com)

![Image](https://cdn.statcdn.com/Statistic/300000/300419-blank-754.png?utm_source=chatgpt.com)

![Image](https://www.rba.gov.au/education/images/explainers/graph-1-australia-and-the-global-economy-the-terms-of-trade-boom.png?utm_source=chatgpt.com)

### 🔹 TOT strongly drives:

* AUDUSD
* Australia nominal GDP
* State revenues
* Equity market (materials & miners)

### **Thumb rule:**

**+10% increase in iron ore ≈ ~1–1.5% appreciation in AUDUSD** (not linear, but strong).

**Trade:**

* Long AUDUSD vs CNH during iron ore rallies
* AUDCAD vs oil shocks
* Long ASX materials vs iron ore momentum

